---
import PageLayout from "@/layouts/Base.astro";

const meta = {
	description:
		"Learn about the @cowsayco community‚Äîporting developer culture to the blockchain. What started as a 1999 CLI joke is now a self-sustaining ecosystem for the modern engineer.",
	title: "About",
};
---

<PageLayout meta={meta}>
	<!-- Version Tag -->
	<div class="mb-8 font-mono text-xs text-textColor/60">
		<span>COWSAY.FARM v1.0.0</span>
	</div>

	<!-- Section 1: The Origin Story (The "Man Page") -->
	<section class="mb-16">
		<h1 class="title mb-6 font-mono">üêÑ ABOUT</h1>
		<p class="mb-4">
			We are porting developer culture to the blockchain. What started as a 1999 CLI joke is now a
			self-sustaining ecosystem for the modern engineer.
		</p>
		<p class="mb-4">
			The original <a
				class="cactus-link"
				href="https://github.com/tnalpgge/rank-amateur-cowsay">cowsay</a
			> command-line program was written in 1999 by Tony Monroe. It generated ASCII art of a cow
			saying a message, becoming an instant classic in developer circles. Two decades later, we're
			bringing that same irreverent spirit to Web3‚Äînot as a novelty, but as a home for dev jokes,
			community, and sustainable economics.
		</p>
	</section>

	<!-- Section 2: The Manifesto (Core Principles) -->
	<section class="mb-16">
		<h2 class="title mb-6 font-mono text-2xl">PRINCIPLES</h2>
		<div class="space-y-6">
			<blockquote class="border-l-4 border-accent pl-6 font-mono text-sm">
				<strong class="block mb-2">Community-First Architecture</strong>
				The token, NFTs, and merch are tools to support and grow the community, not the other way
				around.
			</blockquote>
			<blockquote class="border-l-4 border-accent pl-6 font-mono text-sm">
				<strong class="block mb-2">Developer Culture Preservation</strong>
				We celebrate the joys, struggles, and humor of being a developer. Every quote, meme, and
				conversation reflects the real developer experience.
			</blockquote>
			<blockquote class="border-l-4 border-accent pl-6 font-mono text-sm">
				<strong class="block mb-2">On-Chain Verifiability</strong>
				All financial operations, wallet balances, and transactions are publicly disclosed so the
				community knows exactly how resources are being used.
			</blockquote>
			<blockquote class="border-l-4 border-accent pl-6 font-mono text-sm">
				<strong class="block mb-2">Long-Term Uptime</strong>
				We're building for the long term. Revenue from merchandise and NFTs supports the ecosystem,
				with tokenomics designed to benefit long-term community members. For specific mechanisms,
				see the <a class="cactus-link" href="/token/">Token</a> page.
			</blockquote>
			<blockquote class="border-l-4 border-accent pl-6 font-mono text-sm">
				<strong class="block mb-2">Joy by Default</strong>
				We bring laughter to developers' daily routines, creating moments of happiness in the daily
				grind.
			</blockquote>
		</div>
	</section>

	<!-- Section 3: The Architecture (The Ecosystem) -->
	<section class="mb-16">
		<h2 class="title mb-6 font-mono text-2xl">ECOSYSTEM</h2>
		<p class="mb-8 text-textColor/80">
			A simplified map of how the components interact:
		</p>
		<div class="grid grid-cols-1 gap-6 md:grid-cols-2">
			<div class="rounded-lg border border-accent bg-accent/5 p-6">
				<h3 class="mb-3 font-mono text-lg font-semibold">Bot</h3>
				<p class="mb-4 text-sm text-textColor/80">
					Daily developer quotes on Twitter. The content engine that powers the ecosystem.
				</p>
			</div>
			<div class="rounded-lg border border-accent bg-accent/5 p-6">
				<h3 class="mb-3 font-mono text-lg font-semibold">Token</h3>
				<p class="mb-4 text-sm text-textColor/80">
					Community participation and value alignment. Built on Solana with transparent
					tokenomics. <a class="cactus-link text-xs" href="/token/">Details ‚Üí</a>
				</p>
			</div>
			<div class="rounded-lg border border-accent bg-accent/5 p-6">
				<h3 class="mb-3 font-mono text-lg font-semibold">NFTs</h3>
				<p class="mb-4 text-sm text-textColor/80">
					Quote artwork as collectibles. Each NFT is a piece of developer culture.
					<a class="cactus-link text-xs" href="/nfts/">Browse ‚Üí</a>
				</p>
			</div>
			<div class="rounded-lg border border-accent bg-accent/5 p-6">
				<h3 class="mb-3 font-mono text-lg font-semibold">Shop</h3>
				<p class="mb-4 text-sm text-textColor/80">
					Merchandise revenue supports the ecosystem. Profits feed back into sustainable
					economics. <a class="cactus-link text-xs" href="/shop/">Visit ‚Üí</a>
				</p>
			</div>
		</div>
		<p class="mt-6 text-sm text-textColor/60">
			Revenue from Shop and NFTs supports sustainable economics. See the
			<a class="cactus-link" href="/token/">Token</a> page for specific mechanisms.
		</p>
	</section>

	<!-- Section 4: The Team/Socials -->
	<section>
		<h2 class="title mb-6 font-mono text-2xl">COMMUNITY</h2>
		<p class="mb-6 text-textColor/80">
			Who is behind the cow? Join the community:
		</p>
		<div class="space-y-3 font-mono text-sm">
			<div class="rounded border border-accent bg-accent/5 p-4">
				<code class="text-textColor/60">$</code>
				<a
					class="cactus-link ml-2"
					href="https://twitter.com/intent/user?screen_name=cowsayco"
					target="_blank"
					rel="noopener noreferrer"
				>
					follow --twitter @cowsayco
				</a>
			</div>
			<div class="rounded border border-accent bg-accent/5 p-4">
				<code class="text-textColor/60">$</code>
				<a
					class="cactus-link ml-2"
					href="https://x.com/i/communities/2011240178778607815"
					target="_blank"
					rel="noopener noreferrer"
				>
					join --twitter-community
				</a>
			</div>
			<div class="rounded border border-accent bg-accent/5 p-4">
				<code class="text-textColor/60">$</code>
				<a
					class="cactus-link ml-2"
					href="https://discord.gg/yhJ24mCSxd"
					target="_blank"
					rel="noopener noreferrer"
				>
					join --discord
				</a>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>
</PageLayout>
